  href=3D"javascript:GoToSld('slide0013.htm');" id=3DPPTL14>Vehicle 2a vs. =
2b</a></font></div>
  <div id=3DPPTC14 class=3DCTxt style=3D'display:none'><font size=3D2>
  <ul>
   <li>b)</li>
   <li>Each sensor is connected to the motor on the opposite side.</li>
   <li>B works the same as A if the light is directly ahead.</li>
   <li>If light is to the left, the right motor will go faster thus turning=
 the
       vehicle towards the light.</li>
   <li>B will eventually find the source of light.</li>
   <li>a)</li>
   <li>Each sensor is connected to the motor on the same side.</li>
   <li>A stays in places with less light and speeds up in better lit areas.=
</li>
   <li>It will head directly towards the light.</li>
   <li>Light on the left will cause the left motor to move more quickly, th=
us
       turning the vehicle away from the light.</li>
  </ul>
  </font></div>
